{"questionId":"14859798","questionHtml":"<p>By solving the differential equation, show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Condone absence of absolute value signs throughout</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>substituting initial conditions&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;to find the value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>⇒</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>c</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>⇒</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfrac><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;</strong></em>(so&nbsp;<em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>±</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math></strong></em>)</p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>substituting initial conditions&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;to find the value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mn>0</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>⇒</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Candidates may use&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;and correctly obtain&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;leading to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p>after consideration of the boundary conditions. In this case, the absence of absolute value signs should not be condoned until the sign has been resolved.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to rearrange and find an integrating factor&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;so IF&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award<em><strong> A1 </strong></em>for LHS and<em><strong> A1 </strong></em>for RHS.</p>\n<p>substituting initial conditions <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;to find the value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mn>0</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mn>0</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>⇒</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>c</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14859798","referenceCode":"23N.2.AHL.TZ2.9b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"By solving the differential equation, show that y=4-2e-x10.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.18—1st order DE’s – Euler method, variables separable, integrating factor, homogeneous DE using sub y=vx"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}